  "commentary": "**Dealer Hedging Commentary:**\n\nWith SPX at 6575.93 sitting below the GEX flip at 6595, dealers are in positive gamma territory and should be buying this dip to hedge their long gamma positions. The massive +23.8B gamma wall at 6600 creates a strong magnet effect, while the thick positive gamma zone between 6580-6600 suggests dealers will provide significant buying support on any further weakness. The recent GEX surge event combined with the current PIN regime indicates dealers are actively stabilizing price action through contra-trend hedging flows.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect buying support to kick in with upward drift toward the 6595-6600 zone.",
